Secrets Manager → protects lifecycle + access + rotation

💥 Why AWS Secrets Manager exists

Because it solves problems Terraform does NOT solve:

1. Centralized secret storage

Instead of embedding secrets in infrastructure state.

2. Access control (IAM-based)

You can say:

EC2 role → can read secret
Terraform → can read secret
Developer → cannot

3. Rotation (BIG reason)

Secrets Manager supports:

automatic password rotation
database credential rotation without downtime

☁️ AWS password rotation (real-world)

Using AWS Secrets Manager, you can enable:

automatic rotation every X days (e.g., 30, 60, 90)
Lambda function handles updating DB password
apps keep working without downtime

✅ Automatic rotation (AWS way)

AWS uses a Lambda rotation function behind the scenes.

Flow:

Secrets Manager
      ↓
Generates new password
      ↓
Rotation Lambda runs
      ↓
Updates database password
      ↓
Updates secret in Secrets Manager

Terraform does NOT do this.

4. Audit tracking

You get:

who accessed secret
when
from where

Terraform state does not give this level of audit control.

5. Separation of concerns

| System          | Purpose                     |
| --------------- | --------------------------- |
| Terraform       | Infrastructure provisioning |
| Secrets Manager | Secret lifecycle management |

-------------------------------------------------
+----------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Feature        | Secrets Manager                                                          | KMS                                                                      |
+----------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| What it stores | Actual secrets (DB passwords, API keys, tokens)                         | Encryption keys only (never plaintext secrets)                           |
+----------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Purpose        | Secret storage + lifecycle management                                   | Cryptographic key management (encrypt/decrypt)                           |
+----------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Rotation       | Built-in automatic rotation (Lambda-based)                              | No rotation of data itself; supports key rotation (annual)               |
+----------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Retrieval      | Returns the actual secret value via API/SDK                             | Returns encrypted/decrypted data, not "secrets"                          |
+----------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Under the hood | Uses KMS internally to encrypt stored secrets at rest                   | Provides the CMK (Customer Master Key) that Secrets Manager uses          |
+----------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Cost           | ~$0.40 per secret/month + API calls                                     | ~$1 per key/month + per-request charges                                  |
+----------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Typical use    | App needs DB password at runtime                                        | Encrypting S3 buckets, EBS volumes, envelope encryption                  |
+----------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+

